  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">R&#xE9;ponse d&#x2019;urgence aux besoins en mati&#xE8;re d&#x2019;eau potable, d&#x2019;hygi&#xE8;ne et d&#x2019;assainissement des d&#xE9;plac&#xE9;s nig&#xE9;rians, des d&#xE9;plac&#xE9;s internes et des communaut&#xE9;s h&#xF4;tes, dans la r&#xE9;gion de Diffa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to water was cited as the highest priority in terms of needs by refugees and internally displaced people in Niger.  UNICEF proposes to use CERF funds to increase the access to water and to improve the hygiene and sanitation needs for those who fled the Boko Haram in Niger as part of a multi sectoral approach.  15 water points will be constructed benefiting 60,000 people.  CERF funded activities will take place over 4 months</narrative>
  </description>
